## 4. Real-World Mapping Example

### **Scenario: TechWorks Sales Process**

Let's map a real business scenario to Salesforce objects:

```
ACCOUNT: Microsoft
├── Industry: Software/Technology
├── Revenue: $198B
├── Number of Employees: 220,000
└── Account Owner: Sarah Johnson

    CONTACT 1: Bill Gates
    ├── Job Title: Founder
    ├── Email: bill@microsoft.com
    └── Reports To: Satya Nadella

    CONTACT 2: Satya Nadella
    ├── Job Title: CEO
    ├── Email: satya@microsoft.com
    └── Department: Executive

    CONTACT 3: Amy Hood
    ├── Job Title: CFO
    ├── Email: amy@microsoft.com
    └── Department: Finance

        OPPORTUNITY 1: Microsoft - Cloud Services Contract
        ├── Amount: $5,000,000
        ├── Stage: Proposal
        ├── Probability: 60%
        ├── Close Date: July 31, 2026
        ├── Primary Contact: Satya Nadella
        └── Products: Azure Cloud Services, Enterprise Support

        OPPORTUNITY 2: Microsoft - AI Integration Project
        ├── Amount: $2,500,000
        ├── Stage: Negotiation
        ├── Probability: 80%
        ├── Close Date: June 15, 2026
        ├── Primary Contact: Bill Gates
        └── Products: AI Solutions, Training, Consulting
```

**Key Relationships:**
- One Account (Microsoft) has **multiple Contacts** (Bill, Satya, Amy)
- One Account (Microsoft) has **multiple Opportunities** (Cloud Services, AI Integration)
- Each Opportunity is linked to an Account and one or more Contacts
- The Account Owner manages the overall relationship

